# Workflow Rules

## Issues
- Every PR must be tied to a GitHub issue.
- Start work by selecting an issue and linking it in the PR.
- If there is not an issue in GitHub ask if you should create one.

## Start Work Checklist
- Ensure local `main` is current before branching.
- Create a branch before making changes (follow naming rules below).

## Branch Naming
Branch names must include the issue ID and use one of:
- `feature/<issue-id>`
- `infrastructure/<issue-id>`
- `bug/<issue-id>`
- `docs/<issue-id>`

## PR Description
All descriptions are managed by Cursor BugBot - just create the PR with no description.